Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: The Smoot-Hawley Tariff Act of 1930
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydlyc
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 17 Dec 1982
The Smoot-Hawley Tariff Act, which forced foreign automobile manufacturers to build their models for export to America in America, with American parts and labour.